{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c1e458ea-c66e-49d7-b142-9992ad98fadc","agentId":"a002fd8396e327964","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You need to fix one issue in a migration file for a Laravel 12 project.\n\n## Fix Required\n\nFile: `C:/Users/sergio/gestor-proyectos/database/migrations/2026_03_25_000000_create_activity_logs_table.php`\n\nChange `cascadeOnDelete()` to `nullOnDelete()` on the user_id foreign key:\n\n**Current (line 14):**\n```php\n$table->foreignId('user_id')->nullable()->constrained()->cascadeOnDelete();\n```\n\n**Should be:**\n```php\n$table->foreignId('user_id')->nullable()->constrained()->nullOnDelete();\n```\n\n**Why:** `activity_logs` is an audit trail. Cascading deletes would destroy historical records when a user is deleted, defeating the purpose. `nullOnDelete()` preserves log entries while clearing the user_id (the column is already nullable, and the controller handles `$log->user?->name ?? 'Sistema'` for null user_id).\n\n## Steps\n\n1. Edit the migration file to change `cascadeOnDelete()` to `nullOnDelete()`\n2. Re-run migration fresh to verify:\n   ```bash\n   cd C:/Users/sergio/gestor-proyectos\n   php artisan migrate:fresh\n   ```\n   Expected: migrates cleanly without errors.\n3. Commit:\n   ```bash\n   git add database/migrations/2026_03_25_000000_create_activity_logs_table.php\n   git commit -m \"fix: use nullOnDelete for activity_logs user_id to preserve audit history\"\n   ```\n\nWork from: `C:/Users/sergio/gestor-proyectos`\n\n## Report Format\n- **Status:** DONE | BLOCKED\n- Files changed\n- Migration output"},"uuid":"cd75512d-9596-4f75-826c-20f787793ed0","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:31:55.319Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"C:\\Users\\sergio\\gestor-proyectos","sessionId":"6a54ed9b-80df-4230-a48d-b2865dd1840b","version":"2.1.78","gitBranch":"punto-2","slug":"logical-churning-hopcroft"}
